name: DeliverableDetails-TaskBackground
ga:eventLabel: Welcome to Regional Design Associates. My name is Maggie Wilkins, and I am Regional Design Associate’s community facilitator for the project you'll be working on. I'm in charge of communications between the firm and the community, and I will oversee your work as an intern. You'll be working on a team of interns, and your team will be assigned an RDA planning consultant. Your team members are: TEAMMATES. Together, you will help our firm create a new zoning plan for the city of Lowell, Massachusetts. At the end of your internship, I will compile your work and submit final zoning recommendations to Curt, the CEO of RDA.

name: Activities-0-NotebookSections-0-SampleSectionText
ga:eventLabel: 1. You will receive an email from Maggie that details the task you need to complete for your internship. 2. You will complete that task according to the email’s instructions. 3. After you complete your task, you will write and submit a notebook entry according to the email’s instructions. This notebook entry is known as a “deliverable" and will appear in your deliverables list. 4. Once every member of your team submits their notebook to Maggie for review, you will receive an email from Maggie that details the next task you need to complete for your internship. You will not be able to proceed to the next step until everyone on your team has submitted a notebook to Maggie. 5. After you have submitted your notebook, Maggie will approve your previous notebook entry or indicate that it needs improvement via email. This may happen before or after you have received the email detailing your next task. 6. If applicable, complete Maggie’s most recent task before completing notebook revisions. Revisions must be submitted to Maggie by 8 AM on the day of the following work session.This cycle will repeat throughout the course of the internship.

The signature is time-stamped and at that point it becomes a legal record with two people who can testify to its accuracy (you and I).

name: active.room.EmailTexts.InviteEmail.NotebookInstructions.ClosingText
ga:eventLabel: It may seem strange to compose a notebook entry for every task you complete, but this is how Regional Design Associates documents the activities of employees for legal purposes. When you complete your notebook and submit it, WorkPro will route it to your supervisor (me) for witnessing. My signature indicates that the work is approved. The signature is time-stamped and at that point it becomes a legal record with two people who can testify to its accuracy (you and I).

name: Activities-0-DeliverableDetails-TaskBackground
ga:eventLabel: Welcome to Regional Design Associates. My name is Maggie Wilkins, and I am Regional Design Associate’s community facilitator for the project you'll be working on. I'm in charge of communications between the firm and the community, and I will oversee your work as an intern. You'll be working on a team of interns, and your team will be assigned an RDA planning consultant. Your team members are: TEAMMATES. Together, you will help our firm create a new zoning plan for the city of Lowell, Massachusetts. At the end of your internship, I will compile your work and submit final zoning recommendations to Curt, the CEO of RDA.
